definition.value: Sexual intercourse in which some anatomical structure is stimulated by the feet.
A non-penetrative sexual practice with the feet that involves one's feet being rubbed on a partner in order to induce sexual excitement, stimulation or orgasm.
Stimulation of genitals by two or more people who stimulate themselves or one another. Such acts may be penetrative, non-penetrative, or both.
The insertion of a body part or other object into a body orifice, such as the vagina, anus or mouth, as part of sexual behavior.
The insertion of a body part or other object into the anus as part of sexual behavior.
The insertion of a body part or other object into the vagina as part of sexual behavior.
The insertion of a body part or other object into the mouth as part of sexual behavior.
The insertion of the penis into the vagina as part of sexual behavior.
The first moment of initial entry of the erect penis into the vagina.
Sexual intercourse in which an object (usually a kind a sex toy) is inserted into the vagina.
Any of various physical configurations that the human body can take.
Positions which people may adopt during or for the purpose of sexual intercourse or other sexual activities.
Sex positions involving exactly two participants.
Sex positions involving more than two participants.
Sexual intercourse in which some anatomical structure is stimulated by the thighs.
Intercourse in which the penis is stimulated by placing it between another individual's thighs.
Sex positions involving three persons.
Sex positions involving four persons.
A sex position which can only be penetrative in nature.
A sex position which may or may not be penetrative in nature.
A sex position which can only be non-penetrative in nature.
A sex position in which the receptive vaginal partner lies on their back and the penetrating partner lies on top of them so that they are facing each other when engaging in vaginal intercourse.
Sex positions which involve oral intercourse.
Sex positions which involve vaginal intercourse.
Sex positions which involve anal intercourse.
Modification of the execution of an event or a process.
Positive modulation of the execution of a process.
Negative modulation of the execution of a process.
Any stimulus (including bodily contact) that leads to, enhances and maintains sexual arousal, and may lead to orgasm.
Any stimulus involving physical contact that leads to, enhances and maintains sexual arousal, and may lead to orgasm.
Any stimulus involving physical contact with the genitals that leads to, enhances and maintains sexual arousal, and may lead to orgasm.
Any stimulus involving physical contact with areas other than the genitals that leads to, enhances and maintains sexual arousal, and may lead to orgasm.
Any stimulus involving physical contact of the genitals with another's mouth that leads to, enhances and maintains sexual arousal, and may lead to orgasm.
Oral stimulation of the clitoris primarily using the tongue and lips.
Oral stimulation of the penis primarily using the tongue and lips.
The insertion of a finger or fingers into an orifice (for example, the vagina or anus) as part of sexual behavior.
The insertion of a finger or fingers into the anus as part of sexual behavior.
A relationship involving some kind of sexual intimacy.
A relationship of mutual affection between people which includes a stronger form of interpersonal bond than an association.
A very close but typically non-sexual relationship between friends, often involving a degree of physical closeness beyond that which is common in a given societal structure.

In historical scholarship, the term may be used to describe a very close relationship between people of the same sex during a period of history when homosexuality did not exist as a social category. In this regard, the term was coined in the later 20th century in order to retrospectively describe a type of relationship which until the mid-19th century had been considered unremarkable but since the second half of the 19th century had become more rare as physical intimacy between non-sexual partners came to be regarded with anxiety.
Any of various disorders affecting the length of the menstrual cycle.
An interpersonal relationship based upon a mutually agreed-upon commitment to one another involving love, trust, honesty, openness, or some other behavior.
An interpersonal relationship which is considered, subjectively, long term.
An interpersonal relationship involving simultaneous or alternating emotions of love and hate—something particularly common when emotions are intense.
A relationship led by a woman.
A relationship led by a man.
A relationship based on mutual romantic love.
A close relationship which is non-sexual and non-romantic.
An interpersonal relationship in which the parties involved live together.
A person with whom one shares a living facility such as a room or dormitory typically without being family or romantically involved.
